duck-lang
------------------------------------------
A simple scripting language based on the idea of duck-typing (or dynamic
typing).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libGL1-23.3.6-1
  libSDL1.2_0-1.2.15-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  libGL-devel-23.3.6-1
  libSDL-devel-1.2.15-3
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/gregtour/duck-lang/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/gregtour/duck-lang/archive/refs/tags/1.00.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack duck-lang-1.00-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./duck-lang-1.00-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/duck-lang-1.00-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/duck-lang-1.00-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(duck-lang)
  /usr/bin/duck.exe
  /usr/bin/gduck.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/duck-lang.README
  /usr/share/doc/duck-lang/README.md

------------------

